7 An Act relating to pharmacy technicians; providing
for pharmacy technician training guidelines;
8 providing for initial training skills; providing for
on-the-job training; requiring approval by the
9 Oklahoma State Board of Pharmacy; requiring liability
insurance with respect to youth apprentices;
10 providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 353.18B of Title 59, unless
16 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. Pharmacy technician applicants who are seventeen (17) years
18 of age or older and enrolled in a youth apprenticeship program for
19 pharmacy technicians or a pharmacy technician training program
20 through the Oklahoma Department of Career and Technology Education
21 shall complete Phase II pharmacy technician training in a pharmacy
22 without the requirement to be a pharmacy employee. All pharmacy
23 technician training programs shall be approved by the Oklahoma State
24 Board of Pharmacy initially and on an annual basis. This permit
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1585 Page 1
1 will only be used for educational purposes for those enrolled in an
2 Oklahoma State Board of Pharmacy approved program.
3 B. The youth apprenticeship program for pharmacy technicians
4 and pharmacy technician training programs through the Oklahoma
5 Department of Career and Technology Education shall carry liability
6 insurance on the students in the respective program that covers the
7 student anywhere the student is training in a pharmacy.
8 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
9 Passed the House of Representatives the 27th day of March, 2025.
